---
import ContentPage from '../layouts/ContentPage.astro';
import { languageAlternates } from '../lib/i18n';

const description =
  'Corporate LLM: a company LLM stack you control. Private or open models, RAG over your data, access control, cost limits, and ops under your policies.';

const alternates = languageAlternates('/corporate-llm/', '/de/corporate-llm/');

const jsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@graph': [
    {
      '@type': 'WebPage',
      '@id': 'https://larsullrich.de/corporate-llm/#webpage',
      url: 'https://larsullrich.de/corporate-llm/',
      name: 'Corporate LLM',
      description,
      inLanguage: 'en',
      isPartOf: { '@id': 'https://larsullrich.de/#website' },
      author: { '@id': 'https://larsullrich.de/#person' },
      about: {
        '@type': 'DefinedTerm',
        name: 'Corporate LLM',
        description,
      },
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Service',
      '@id': 'https://larsullrich.de/corporate-llm/#service',
      name: 'Corporate LLM',
      url: 'https://larsullrich.de/corporate-llm/',
      description,
      provider: { '@id': 'https://larsullrich.de/#person' },
      areaServed: ['DE', 'EU', 'Worldwide'],
      serviceType: 'Corporate LLM platform build',
    },
  ],
};
---

<ContentPage
  title="Corporate LLM - Lars Ullrich"
  description={description}
  canonical="/corporate-llm/"
  noteId="corporate-llm"
  heading="Corporate LLM"
  eyebrow="Service · Platform"
  lead="A company LLM stack on your terms: data residency, access, cost, and who gets paged when it breaks."
  icon="/graphics/icon-model-orbits.svg"
  alternates={alternates}
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
  localeSwitch={{ href: '/de/corporate-llm/', label: 'Deutsch' }}
>
  <p>
    Most companies do not need another consumer chatbot. They need an LLM stack that runs on their terms. That is a Corporate LLM. Project engagement, typically 6-12 weeks.
  </p>

  <h2>What gets built</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Model choice: hosted APIs where they fit, open-weight models you host when data, cost, or lock-in require it</li>
    <li>RAG and tools over your documents and systems, with clear boundaries</li>
    <li>Access control, audit trails, and rate or budget limits</li>
    <li>Ops: monitoring, evals, and a path to keep it running after launch</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How this differs from a Build Sprint</h2>
  <p>
    A Build Sprint ships one product system with AI inside it. Corporate LLM is the shared company capability: the platform internal teams (and sometimes customers) use under your policies. Same engineering bar. Different scope.
  </p>

  <h2>Where to start</h2>
  <p>
    Unsure whether you need a platform or a single use case? Start with the
    <a href="/services/readiness-audit/">Readiness &amp; Production Audit</a>.
    Already clear you need a private or hybrid LLM stack? This engagement.
  </p>
</ContentPage>
